window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>The Immortality Blues</i> opens on New Earth where we find Vito Martino, immortal after his life was saved by the super being Defender-11.</p> <p>But pondering living on while his friends and family members age and die has put him in a funk.</p> <p>So, Defender-11attempts to cheer him up by sending Vito on multiple missions, back in time on Earth where he will witness history and attempt to undo some of the wrongs the evil one, Defender-4, had done in the past.</p> <p>Vito meets famous people and others, influencing history in subtle and surprising ways. Founding fathers? Check. Jesus Christ? Of course. Inimitably, Vito's interactions with benevolent and malevolent beings combine humor, savvy, and action.</p> <p>Upnick connects these adventures with episodes from the five previous books in the Time Will Tell series.&nbsp;</p> <p>Through time and space, friendships endure through danger and joy. Upnick's memorable characters make <i>The Immortality Blues</i> a gripping continuation of his epic series.</p>"; 
